00:24:45,741 --> 00:24:47,742
So that sounds obvious, it's a platform game,

524
00:24:47,762 --> 00:24:49,903
but actually we had to remind ourselves that

525
00:24:50,043 --> 00:24:51,304
the gadget should be there to support

526
00:24:51,324 --> 00:24:53,824
the core of the gameplay, which is jumping around.

527
00:24:53,905 --> 00:24:57,626
So here you can see how the shurikens are used

528
00:24:58,326 --> 00:24:59,407
as a way to make a platform.

529
00:25:00,907 --> 00:25:02,488
And here is the water gadget,

530
00:25:04,429 --> 00:25:09,090
also used as a way to make platforms for Astro.

531
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:10,451
So always as a complement to platforming.

532
00:25:13,015 --> 00:25:15,976
And that's really interesting because it creates a kind of turn-based approach

533
00:25:16,016 --> 00:25:18,697
whereby you have this kind of first-person interaction with the controllers

534
00:25:19,197 --> 00:25:21,137
and then you have some jumping, jumping, jumping around.

535
00:25:21,217 --> 00:25:22,758
First-person interaction, jumping, jumping.

